      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:4:14:5",
      "text": [
        " انْظُرْ قَلْبَكَ فَإِنْ أَنْكَرَ صَاحِبَكَ فَاعْلَمْ أَنَّ أَحَدَكُمَا قَدْ أَحْدَثَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Zanar Bin Suweyd, from Al Qasim Bin Suleyman, from Jarrah Al Madainy, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Look at your heart, for if it rejects your companion, then know that one of you has done something wrong’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "5. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from al-Al-Nadr ibn Suwayd from al-Qasim ibn Sulayman from Jarrah al-Mada’ini from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “See your heart. If it dislikes your friend then notice that one of you have done something newly wrong.’” "
        ]
      }
